lt social care: understanding the challenges to local third sector infrastructure organisations</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/H038426/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>This Fellowship is a joint initiative between the Centre for Regional Economic and Social Research (CRESR) at Sheffield Hallam University and four South Yorkshire third sector infrastructure organisations: the 'Voluntary Actions' in Rotherham, Barnsley and Sheffield, and Doncaster Council of Voluntary Services. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The Fellowship will support a programme of collaborative research aimed at enhancing the partners' understanding of the challenges and opportunities facing local infrastructure organisations following the implementation of individual budgets. Individual budgets are a central feature of the government's 'personalisation' agenda in adult social care which aims to provide a more personal service and give service users more control over the treatment they receive. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The Fellowship will involve a number of research tasks including a review of existing policy and research material, interviews with key staff and stakeholders across the partner organisations, and case study fieldwork in three of the individual budget pilot local authority areas. Through the research the partner organisations aim to improve their understanding of the impact that individual budgets and the personalisation agenda will have on their work. They will use the evidence collected to develop strategies to support their third sector members meet the challenges presented by individual budgets and the personalisation agenda.&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2010-05-21</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2010-02-22</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>7600</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Understanding personalisation</gtr:description><gtr:form>A talk or presentation</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>Regional</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>8E2D0674-F03A-45E2-8ABE-E1E9FF708506</gtr:id><gtr:impact>These are the slides from a presentation given to an audience of public sector and voluntary sector practioners in The Humber on 9 March 2011. Different iterations of this presentation have also been given in Rotherham, Sheffield and Canrbridge in the past 12 months.

A further presentation was given in Southampton in June 2011.</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>r-4527583675.9503772b043646</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Policymakers/parliamentarians</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:year>2011</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput></gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:impactSummaryOutput><gtr:description>To revise voluntary sector infrastructure services in South Yorkshire</gtr:description><gtr:firstYearOfImpact>2010</gtr:firstYearOfImpact><gtr:id>B5F97404-FF05-4D38-BB56-CC15EC8BBE1C</gtr:id><gtr:impactTypes/><gtr:outcomeId>5457abd72f9a08.83627794</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sector>Healthcare</gtr:sector></gtr:impactSummaryOutput></gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:description>The research found that personalisation represents a series of threats, challenges, and opportunities, all of which have considerable implications for frontline third sector organisations and local infrastructure organisations and the ways in which they

carry-out their work. 



These threats, challenges and opportunities must be considered in two ways:



? in terms of organisational development: in particular the different stages of development that exist within frontline TSOs in relation to personalisation, and



? in terms of the challenges frontline TSOs face: in particular the distinction between the environmental and operational factors which have the potential to limit progress.



